Music Video
 &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; was accompanied by a music video for its single release. The music video was shot on July 29, 2009.17 The music video was directed by Trudy Bellinger.
The music video takes on an urban theme to it and sees the girls in a house and around a city singing. The video involves no dance routines and ends with the girls leaving a nightclub. During Una Healy's middle eight of the song the girls can be seen bathed in atmospheric blue lighting whilst wearing black outfits. Other scenes include Mollie King licking her thumb and smearing her heart-shaped tattoo saying 'Forever' as a metaphor for saying that &quot;Forever Is Over&quot;. In another seen Una can be seen deleting the L from 'lover' to spell 'over' on her laptop, also as a metaphor to contrast with the song's title.
Promotion
The single was also performed at various British music festivals and on various television shows as promotion during its release period. On September 12, &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; was played live for the first time at the Annual Freedom Festival held in Hull.18 Later that month, on September 28 the group was interviewed on The Paul O'Grady Show where they performed &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; for the first time on live television.19 On October 3, a day before the release of &quot;Forever Is Over,&quot; the girls performed at G-A-Y in London.20 A day after the single's physical CD release, the band performed the song on ITV1's This Morning. On the same day the girls were interviewed on The 5:19 Show where an exclusive acoustic performance of &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; was recorded.21 The group then appeared on October 12 for a performance of the song on The Alan Titchmarsh Show.22 October 17, the group performed at the Hollyoaks Music Festival which saw the group perform &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; as well the title track from their second album.23 The group then performed the single along with the album track &quot;Deeper&quot; and their previous single &quot;Issues&quot; as part of 'The Biz Sessions' for British newspaper The Sun on October 19.24 On November 6, the group performed at the premiere of Disney film &quot;A Christmas Carol&quot; alongside R&amp;B singer songwriter Taio Cruz and on November 14 the girls performed at &quot;The Christmas Lights&quot; at Cheshire Oaks.25 On November 29 the girls performed &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; on T4's Stars of 2009 alongside British hip hop trio N-Dubz at Earl's Court in London.26
