&quot;Forever Is Over&quot; debuted and peaked on the Irish Singles Chart, issued October 8, at number nine. It was the second highest new entry of the week. The single spent a total of five weeks within the chart29 and gave the group their second Irish top ten hit after Comic Relief single &quot;Just Can't Get Enough&quot; peaked at number six in March 2009. On October 11, &quot;Forever Is Over&quot; debuted and peaked at number two on the UK Singles Chart.30 The single became the group's fifth top ten hit and second single to reach a peak of number two in the United Kingdom.
